    ],
    "lyrics": {
      "text": "By con-ceiv--ing the Wis--dom and Word of God in thy womb,__ with-out be--ing con-sumed there-by, thou bar--est for all the world Him Who fill-eth the u-ni-verse; thou hast held in thine arms__ Him that hold-eth to-geth-er all, Who hath fash-ioned cre-a--tion and giv-eth their food to all. Where-fore, I be-seech thee,__ O thou all-ho-ly vir-gin and Moth--er of God, that I be re-deemed from my man-y sins when I shall have to stand be--fore the Face of my Cre-a-tor and God; O pure La-dy Vir-gin, help me in that__ hour, for thou canst do what-so-ev--er thou dost will, O all--hymned__ Maid."
    }
  }
}